GamesRegularyPlayed: DOTA 2, Resident Evil, GTA V, The Elder Scrolls (all parts), Mass Effect, DayZ
DS: High temporal accuracy and spatial accuracy needed. High consequences of permadeath and important actions.
TA: Lots of players moving around a lot. High DoF.
PR: Battle Royale with a 100 players, big map. Map predictability cannot compensate for random player encounters.
DoF: Mouse and keyboard have 4 directions each.
CQ: End of round in case of death.
IoA: Not placing a shot fast enough or building a cover can result in death.
FF: Hit feedback and preview of built structures allow players to stop or continue with action.
ToI: Continuous for aiming and discontinous for running/stopping.
Open: Severity of punishment for incorrect action (lost game - lost rank in leadership board.)
